Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:36.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.48,0:03:38.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll knock you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.94,0:03:40.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, no, Sera{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.45,0:03:45.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that person! The one\NSonoko wanted you to meet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.99,0:03:50.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My boyfriend, Makoto Kyogoku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:53.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This girl is my classmate, Masumi Sera{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:56.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're a girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:03:58.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:02.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were some insolent guy\Nwho was getting overly friendly with Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.55,0:04:07.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it! I'm always being mistaken for a guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:10.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Sonoko! You should have stopped them earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.31,0:04:15.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wanted to see those two fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.27,0:04:17.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, what would you've done if one of them got hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.27,0:04:16.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Kyogoku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.36,0:04:18.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Here's your glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:19.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.40,0:04:20.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I'm much obliged.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.23,0:04:21.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's no biggie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:25.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to try fighting him a little more too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.07,0:04:25.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.62,0:04:29.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeet Kune Do... Who taught you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.62,0:04:34.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My older brother! Well, my brother was\Nthree times stronger than me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:35.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:39.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say your older brother was dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:41.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's what I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:46.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But weren't you talking on the phone\Nwith your brother the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.39,0:04:50.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you overheard that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.35,0:04:53.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:56.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My smart second-oldest brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:04:59.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He takes after our father,\Nunlike my late brother and me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:01.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he doesn't look like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.36,0:05:06.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems that he's in the middle\Nof an important job right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:08.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he won't even tell me where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.91,0:05:12.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he sometimes advises me\Non a case on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:18.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,During the case the other day he also told me\Nthat my deduction was unreliable,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.63,0:05:22.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but since you were there to\Ncome to the rescue if I was wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:26.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, not me, but Shinichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.39,0:05:33.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be that she knows I'm Shin'ichi Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.06,0:05:37.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.90,0:05:41.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something go wrong\Nwhen you washed that shirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:43.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Go wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.11,0:05:48.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The collar is so wide, your underwear is visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.66,0:05:53.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's called off-shoulder and it's done on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:55.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm showing it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.70,0:05:57.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Showing it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:06:01.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That underwear is meant to be shown off?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.46,0:06:03.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.59,0:06:07.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko got all dressed up for you, Kyogoku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:13.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, Kyogoku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there's blood\Ncoming from the back of your right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.43,0:06:15.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that when you\Nfought Sera{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.93,0:06:17.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, no, this is from outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.89,0:06:18.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:23.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I'm sorry about earlier! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.44,0:06:23.44,Character Card,,0000,0000,0150,,{\fad(300,0)}Michiko Mon'na (30)\NMiddle School Math Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.69,0:06:27.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. My wounds are very shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.11,0:06:28.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, how is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.90,0:06:31.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's fine. He's simply suffering\Nthe consequences of his actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An acquaintance is taking him home in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.45,0:06:35.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:39.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I went to buy some\Nclothes to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge into earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.21,0:06:41.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I became entangled with an\Nacquaintance of this woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:43.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he punched me in the solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:48.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}He may not look it, but he\Nteaches PE at a middle school!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.51,0:06:50.26,Character Card,,0000,0110,0150,,{\fad(275,275)}Sunami Masaki (29)\NMiddle School Science Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.97,0:06:51.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Usually Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is an\Nearnest, steady teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.47,0:06:55.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but when he drinks, he\Nbecomes a different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:06:57.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.31,0:07:00.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He fell asleep in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.44,0:07:04.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In his sleep, he whispered,\N"I'm going to kill that bastard."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.19,0:07:08.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, what are\Nwe going to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.32,0:07:09.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.78,0:07:13.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were going to have him\Nteach us how to bowl, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.16,0:07:14.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Teachers!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.53,0:07:17.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you could use a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.20,0:07:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not let a guy like me\Nshow you how to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.63,0:07:30.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Use your hips! The hips!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.26,0:07:33.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Move your hips this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.89,0:07:34.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:40.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you hold the ball, the pivot leg, ball,\Nand head all need to be in a straight line, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:41.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:42.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you try!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:51.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.95,0:07:53.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it, magnificent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:08:00.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, to be able to instruct a couple\Nof teachers. It's the highest honour, ladies!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.87,0:08:02.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.63,0:08:09.46,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That guy... He'll be brought in\Nfor sexual harassment one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:19.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.48,0:08:29.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And it seems like this guy will be\Narrested for property damage some day...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:35.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would appear that this sort of\Nfashionable game doesn't suit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.41,0:08:37.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So it seems...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:41.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I only returned to Japan today,\Nso I also have a bit of jet lag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.91,0:08:45.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, why don't you\Ntake a nap in Dad's rental car?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.25,0:08:49.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing how I have the key...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:51.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll take you up on that offer then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:08:57.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I was finally\Non a date with Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:09:00.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, we're going out\Nto dinner afterwards as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.14,0:09:04.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, where are you going, Michiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.31,0:09:06.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to see how Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:08.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a bit worried about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:09.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.40,0:09:11.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be back once he sobers up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:15.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He isn't there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:18.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} wasn't in the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:21.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, seems like he got out of\Nthe car and went somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:25.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why didn't he come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:29.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? Maybe he's sleeping\Nin the shade of some car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.25,0:09:32.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop joking! It's been raining\Nthis whole time, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.96,0:09:35.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.09,0:09:36.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:39.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for someone, why\Ndon't you leave it to me, Kogoro Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:43.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My father is a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.52,0:09:45.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kogoro Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:47.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That famous detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.98,0:09:49.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.81,0:09:51.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.32,0:09:53.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:55.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.86,0:09:58.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.20,0:10:00.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use! He isn't anywhere between the cars!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:04.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that he's in some bar, drinking again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.45,0:10:08.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't drunkenly bothering\Nsomeone else again, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:09.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for him in nearby bars, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.38,0:10:11.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:15.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You guys go looking\Naround drinking places as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.13,0:10:17.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.55,0:10:19.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even know what he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:22.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a picture of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.68,0:10:24.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I send it to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.93,0:10:25.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.89,0:10:30.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, our rental car was also parked here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.40,0:10:31.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.31,0:10:32.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Kyogoku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.69,0:10:39.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... Well, I don't think if Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were to get in a fight,\Nhe'd fight back until they were beaten to a pulp...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.78,0:10:42.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say "beaten to a pulp", at any rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:02.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! He's nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:03.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.30,0:11:06.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't return to the car either!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.35,0:11:08.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He also turned off his mobile phone, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.89,0:11:13.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, where did he disappear to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:18.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's that? What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:25.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I also looked underneath the cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.95,0:11:29.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but it really seems like he isn't\Nanywhere in this parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:31.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then should we ask the police\Nto look for him after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.17,0:11:36.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:40.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The door of the toilet was\Nunlocked, so I opened it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:42.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-And inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.19,0:12:00.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's petechiae on the eyelid and conjunctiva.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.44,0:12:02.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And foam is coming from his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:04.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No facial edema.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.95,0:12:07.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And no sign of strangulation on the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:09.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Death by drowning?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:09.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Death by drowning?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:13.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's also no sign of his having\Nbeen restrained on his arms and legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:16.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and since his clothes are soaking wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:19.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.26,0:12:24.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was carried here after\Nbeing drowned somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.72,0:12:32.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, given the state of the livor mortis and\Nrigor mortis, he was killed about an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.52,0:12:37.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just about the time when we starting looking\Nfor him and went to various drinking places.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:44.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that the killer tossed the corpse\Ninto this toilet and escaped before we returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:45.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:47.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who on earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:52.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This teacher's pretty strongly built,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:57.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it was either a repeat offender,\Nor someone really strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.42,0:12:58.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:05.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.68,0:13:12.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the person who was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.56,0:13:16.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was Masahiro Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 32,\Nwho taught PE at a middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.19,0:13:20.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who found the body
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:25.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was a science teacher from the same\Nmiddle school, Masaki Sunami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:27.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:31.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, could you please tell me\Nhow you found him in more detail, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.37,0:13:33.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:40.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} and I had planned to go\Nbowling together with our colleague, Michiko,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:46.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but drunk from the beer he had drunk on the car ride here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.59,0:13:49.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he started to act violently\Ndowntown. It was quite stressful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.05,0:13:53.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought it might be best to let him sleep it off, so I brought him to Michiko's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:57.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Colleague, you say... Does that mean\Nyou're also a middle school teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.64,0:14:00.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes. I teach math.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.98,0:14:01.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.27,0:14:03.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then? What happened next?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.86,0:14:06.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After Sunami and I had been\Nbowling for about an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:09.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the car to check up on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.53,0:14:14.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had a lot of things going on,\Nso I didn't want to leave him on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:17.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when I came to the car, he wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.50,0:14:20.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Flustered by his disappearance,\Nall of us started looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.54,0:14:22.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you say all of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.34,0:14:26.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At the bowling alley,\Nwe happened to meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.09,0:14:28.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,None other than me, Kogoro Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:31.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what a pleasant surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:35.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So we searched the parking lot,\Nbut didn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.64,0:14:39.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And thinking that he might be getting drunk again in a bar somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:41.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we divided the area between ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.65,0:14:45.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with my daughter and her friends helping out as well,\Nand searched in the bars around here for about an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:48.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but we didn't find him anywhere,\Nso we came back to this parking lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.70,0:14:52.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,thinking that he might have returned to the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:14:57.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And just as we had thought, he had returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:02.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Into this toilet stall on the parking lot,\Nas a cold, drowned corpse, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:03.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Drowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.50,0:15:05.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:09.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Without an autopsy we can't be 100% sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.30,0:15:12.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but going from the state of the body,\Nthat is most likely the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:15.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the estimated time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.51,0:15:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be around 5 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.97,0:15:20.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, 5 PM, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:26.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's around the time when we left this parking lot\Nto look around the various bars, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:26.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:33.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you not look inside the toilet\Nthe first time you searched the parking lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.45,0:15:39.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was locked with a padlock, and an\N"out of order" sign was stuck to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:41.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stuck to the door, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.29,0:15:44.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I saw that too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.63,0:15:50.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when we came to look here for the\Nsecond time that sign had been removed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.13,0:15:52.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and since the padlock was\Nalso nowhere to be seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:56.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-And when I opened the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:59.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.89,0:16:06.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means... Between the time when\NSunami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} accompanied the victim to the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.15,0:16:10.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the time when Michiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} checked up on him\Nan hour later, someone got him away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.53,0:16:15.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then they drowned him while Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand the others were going around the bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.74,0:16:21.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They brought the corpse back here and placed it\Ninside the stall before Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.71,0:16:23.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.33,0:16:28.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what was that about\Nkeeping watch on Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.96,0:16:35.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he becomes like a different person when drunk,\Neasily picking fights with strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.47,0:16:39.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he said he wouldn't drink\Neven one today, but in the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.14,0:16:42.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.27,0:16:45.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a bruise on the victim's abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.73,0:16:46.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bruise?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:48.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.27,0:16:51.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, my bad, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.07,0:16:55.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was drunk and starting an argument\Nover nothing, swung his fist at me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.99,0:16:57.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I hit him in the solar plexus without thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.99,0:16:58.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:02.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He screamed that our eyes\Nhad met, or something similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.91,0:17:06.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a very good-natured person, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.00,0:17:10.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You helped Mr. Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the\Nothers looking for that drunk, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.13,0:17:14.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was taking a nap in Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s car,\Nwhich was parked here, at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:20.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am taking you into custody for murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:25.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, wait a moment, Yamamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:28.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would he really murder someone\Njust because they picked a fight with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.44,0:17:29.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.65,0:17:32.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.98,0:17:37.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He clearly just confessed with\Na cleverness that could rival my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:41.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saying that he has a motive and no alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.08,0:17:45.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's not enough to immediately\Narrest him though, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.71,0:17:48.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's fumbling along as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.50,0:17:54.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?!\NThere's no way Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is guilty!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.88,0:17:59.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you can prove his innocence?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.51,0:18:01.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.10,0:18:05.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because... Because Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.35,0:18:07.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.77,0:18:14.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1000)}Absolutely fantastic and nice and a good person!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:21.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's no proof at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:24.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Yamamura, please look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.99,0:18:27.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a burn mark at the tip of his left shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:32.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This means the victim was probably\Nknocked out with a stun gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:33.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Stun gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.63,0:18:38.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer used a stun gun,\Nthis guy here should be innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.55,0:18:39.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? W-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:45.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he can knock someone out with\Nnothing but a punch to the stomach,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.27,0:18:50.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and since the victim was already bruised\Nthere from the first time he punched him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:53.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if he used a stun gun\Non purpose to make us think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.23,0:19:01.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that he would walk around with a stun\Ngun for protection, seeing how he's a karate master.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:03.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Karate master?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:06.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been winning championships all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:10.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Undefeated in 400 matches,\Nhe's the prince of kicks!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:15.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, you should've said so earliâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.38,0:19:16.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please say so earlier, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.42,0:19:21.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You already met during\Nthe red handkerchief case, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:25.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamamura, are you feeling unwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.14,0:19:31.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sound so formal all of a sudden.\NYou were usually so casual all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.27,0:19:35.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I did that on purpose so people\Nwould let their guard down around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.07,0:19:41.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But as an Inspector I should\Npreserve a certain dignity!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:44.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.03,0:19:48.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if you were here the whole time,\Ndid you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.70,0:19:50.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A suspicious person for example?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:53.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was fast asleep, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.33,0:19:55.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, you were fast asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.34,0:19:59.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.71,0:20:01.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I said stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.09,0:20:06.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.72,0:20:08.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that the ground\Nis inclined downwards here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.89,0:20:14.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there's a slight inclination\Ndue to land subsidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:18.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like they're planning to work\Non the road surface here next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.73,0:20:19.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.44,0:20:22.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Land subsidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.53,0:20:25.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a sec! In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.70,0:20:28.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The slanted dirt marks on this wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.99,0:20:30.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:35.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.54,0:20:37.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! It's raining again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.71,0:20:40.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us go inside the bowling alley for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.59,0:20:42.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can continue our talk there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.64,0:20:53.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:55.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't go soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.48,0:20:55.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:20:59.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a bit strange around the vents there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.28,0:21:04.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the only place where the raindrops don't\Nrun down, but form a sort of ring, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.16,0:21:09.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bit sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:12.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something was affixed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.16,0:21:18.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you guys should also quickly go inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.04,0:21:18.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.38,0:21:29.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The raindrops are similarly repelled around the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.76,0:21:32.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost like it had been weatherized with duct tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.06,0:21:36.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this was a drowning, not a suffocation, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.85,0:21:37.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.10,0:21:42.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the same is not true for the\Nvents at the bottom of the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.65,0:21:46.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's weatherstripping,\Nit makes no sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.70,0:21:48.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.32,0:21:52.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And also, didn't you smell something\Nwhen we first entered the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.58,0:21:54.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:21:55.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The smell of kerosene!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.46,0:21:57.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.42,0:22:01.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you hear me earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:02.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.05,0:22:03.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.16,0:22:30.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He definitely drowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.45,0:22:32.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.53,0:22:33.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.45,0:22:37.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The coroner just informed me that water had\Naccumulated in his respiratory tracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.41,0:22:42.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, even assuming that he\Nwas knocked out with a stun gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.50,0:22:47.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,drowning such a fit man\Nwithout tying him up somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.09,0:22:49.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't you need two\Nor three people for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.47,0:22:50.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.68,0:22:55.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it were a karate master,\None would be more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.97,0:22:58.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that? Are you still\Nsuspecting Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.93,0:22:59.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Not particularly...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.98,0:23:06.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was also informed that there's pressure marks\Nin the form of a line on the corpse's lower abdomen...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.03,0:23:07.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the lower abdomen?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.32,0:23:11.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... There were no such marks on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.16,0:23:15.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So maybe the killer carried the corpse by the belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.41,0:23:17.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.33,0:23:21.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You would need to have quite powerful arms for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.42,0:23:24.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a karate master, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.05,0:23:30.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I said for example. For example.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.22,0:23:37.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, you said that the victim had a lot of\Nthings going on earlier. What did you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.56,0:23:38.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.83,0:23:44.84,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Sunami Masaki (29)\NMiddle School Science Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.83,0:23:44.84,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Michiko Mon'na (30)\NMiddle School Math Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.06,0:23:43.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} and my little\Nsister were planning to marry,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.90,0:23:46.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}but his father was against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.48,0:23:51.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems his parents had already\Narranged for him to marry another girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.86,0:23:54.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When they found out,\Nthe two of them were shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.41,0:23:57.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think they had considered\Neloping at one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.87,0:24:02.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, only my sister killed herself\Nby jumping into the ocean to drown...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.13,0:24:06.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did they talk to you about eloping?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.71,0:24:10.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I got an e-mail from my sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.13,0:24:13.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The two of us are going away together", it said...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.34,0:24:16.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got that mail as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.26,0:24:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since she and I were classmates and best friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.85,0:24:25.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was from that point on, wasn't it? That Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}\Nwould start getting violent when drunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.40,0:24:30.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... That's why, when he\Nwoke up while we were bowling...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.82,0:24:33.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably got into a fight\Nwith someone and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.24,0:24:37.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Do you come often to this bowling alley?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.95,0:24:42.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Since the girl who passed away loved bowling...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.37,0:24:45.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, it rained the last\Nfew times we came here as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.50,0:24:48.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.75,0:24:54.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found a wet towel and four strange empty cans\Nin the bin next to the toilet!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.63,0:24:56.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Empty cans?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.14,0:24:56.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.22,0:24:59.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All four are burned around the opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.43,0:25:03.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it is because someone\Nused them as an ashtray?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.14,0:25:06.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the smell of kerosene comes from inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.81,0:25:07.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kerosene?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.86,0:25:12.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, wait... Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.62,0:25:20.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Forensics Guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.99,0:25:24.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you check it out? That shelf over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.87,0:25:27.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! Kids should be over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.88,0:25:34.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Uncle Kogoro said that there might be\Nsomething in the spare toilet paper roll(s)...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.51,0:25:40.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, what an obstinate boy... But, well, if you say\Nthat Sleeping Kogoro asked you to check it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.10,0:25:44.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Burn marks on the ceiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.64,0:25:46.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Take some pictures!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.48,0:25:47.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.15,0:25:50.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So it's like that after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.77,0:25:55.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That explains why the lower part of the wall\Ninside the toilet was curiously wet like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.28,0:25:59.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no doubt about it!\NThat person was the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.74,0:26:04.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"It seems like he has\Nalso arrived at the truth..."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.87,0:26:12.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"But whether or not our deductions are the same...\NLately I've been losing confidence in that regard..."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.38,0:26:18.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh! That was quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.47,0:26:21.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Who is he?", is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.05,0:26:24.43,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I guess that was to be expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.41,0:26:41.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh! It came!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.49,0:26:47.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"If it's him there's no problem", you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.75,0:26:52.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A fight! It was a fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.29,0:26:55.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The drunken victim who was sleeping in the car
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.92,0:27:00.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,woke up, went to some bar to start drinking again\Nand there it came to a fight with someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.88,0:27:04.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was taken somewhere and killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.05,0:27:09.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, when you and your companions\Nwent around the bars to look for the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.35,0:27:12.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,did not everyone say they had not seen him?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.69,0:27:15.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were probably just playing dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.69,0:27:22.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the bar's reputation would suffer if it came out\Nthat customers had been brawling there!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.45,0:27:26.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why was the killer carrying a stun gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.41,0:27:30.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, where and why\Ndid he drown the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.79,0:27:35.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's absolutely no reason for the killer\Nto leave the corpse in the toilet on the parking lot
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.13,0:27:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where the victim had been sleeping in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.80,0:27:42.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.64,0:27:45.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, the victim, Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.89,0:27:50.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was brought to the car on this\Nparking lot by Masaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} here
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.06,0:27:53.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to sleep off his inebriation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.23,0:27:58.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And before Mon'na{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} went\Nto check on him about an hour later,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.94,0:28:00.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he must have woken up and left the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.53,0:28:04.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And while we went looking for\NTamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} in various bars
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.49,0:28:09.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after hearing that he had disappeared...\NAfter getting into an argument with someone somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.91,0:28:15.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he was drowned, and before we\Ncame back to the parking lot again,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.25,0:28:19.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he was placed inside the toilet on the\Nparking lot. There's no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.67,0:28:25.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you could say that the person who was taking a nap\Nin the car on that same parking lot the whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.01,0:28:28.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this karate guy is suspicious as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.97,0:28:32.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But considering the fact that\Nthe killer used a stun gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.31,0:28:33.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he's completely innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.81,0:28:36.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm saying you should\Nhurry up and go around the bars,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.77,0:28:39.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to properly question people!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.11,0:28:40.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I suppose you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.69,0:28:42.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.53,0:28:44.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The preparations for the experiment are finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.91,0:28:45.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.82,0:28:47.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.41,0:28:51.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the forensics people said that\NDetective Mouri needed it to solve the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.37,0:28:55.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that you had given your permission, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.25,0:28:57.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What're you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.75,0:28:59.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember saying anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.55,0:29:04.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But according to the forensic scientist, this boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.84,0:29:08.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyway, let's go take a look! I love experiments!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.64,0:29:13.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would some shrimp who's in the first year of grade\Nschool even have done an experiment before?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.14,0:29:15.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, but he might have done so at Doc's...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.94,0:29:19.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's go and find out what's going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.19,0:29:20.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.49,0:29:27.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"If it's him there's no problem"?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.45,0:29:29.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.74,0:29:32.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why does my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.49,0:29:34.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}know this kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.55,0:29:44.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.51,0:29:48.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The area around the toilet is totally flooded!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.68,0:29:52.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, but... You ordered us to do so, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.93,0:29:58.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said we should put a towel over the drain\Nto hold back the rain water and let it accumulate...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.23,0:30:04.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, since the ground is inclined\Nhere due to land subsidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.07,0:30:07.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rain that fell until a little\Nwhile ago has accumulated...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.45,0:30:12.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But like this, the valuable\Ncrime scene is completely ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.62,0:30:17.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We transferred the toilet box with the corpse\Nsomewhere else and are in the process of examining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.33,0:30:20.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a different toilet box.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.75,0:30:25.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was also done on Detective Mouri's order.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.71,0:30:28.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As I've said before, I didn't say any suchâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.22,0:30:37.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dad?! There's water gathered there!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.94,0:30:43.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it matter if my pants get wet?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.94,0:30:46.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it helps me verify this trick, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.19,0:30:48.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W=When you say trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.99,0:30:54.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be... that the victim was drowned\Nusing this accumulated rain water?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.20,0:30:59.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it takes quite a while\Nfor this much rain water to gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.67,0:31:02.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, even if the victim\Nwas knocked out by a stun gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.84,0:31:09.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you would need quite a bit of force to drown\Na grown man in this water without binding him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.01,0:31:14.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the killer must have been\Nsomeone rather strong after all, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.14,0:31:17.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nisn't like that, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.22,0:31:18.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.48,0:31:20.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.56,0:31:22.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He ran away!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.06,0:31:23.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let him be!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.27,0:31:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably went to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.44,0:31:28.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He has nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.15,0:31:29.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.24,0:31:34.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because you don't need to be\Nstrong in order to use this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.32,0:31:37.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer locked up the victim in the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.12,0:31:40.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the victim was drowned\Nwithout being touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.42,0:31:43.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.71,0:31:48.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.96,0:31:53.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But seeing is believing,\Nso why don't we try it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.47,0:31:57.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether we can actually drown\Nsomeone inside that toilet...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.93,0:32:01.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, Inspector Yamamura,\Nyou'll be the guinea pig!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.56,0:32:04.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.81,0:32:08.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry... I asked the forensics people\Nto prepare some oxygen for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.61,0:32:12.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that an oxygen flask?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.61,0:32:14.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, tomboy!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.91,0:32:17.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can help set up the trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.87,0:32:20.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You also understood the trick that was used, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.62,0:32:22.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.92,0:32:25.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First the victim is placed in the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.84,0:32:31.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the vents at the back of the box are sealed with tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.51,0:32:36.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, we fill four cans with kerosene\Nand stuff some paper into the opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.97,0:32:38.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After lighting the paper up,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.26,0:32:41.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we place the cans on the rack inside the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.39,0:32:46.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, we only need to close the door\Nand seal the openings with tape...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.81,0:32:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-And how does he drown?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.90,0:32:52.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.71,0:33:06.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.25,0:33:10.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The water doesn't reach farther than my ankles...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.96,0:33:14.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could someone drown like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.63,0:33:18.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's getting rather hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.26,0:33:19.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It went out...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.48,0:33:27.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What was that?!\NWhat just happened inside?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.82,0:33:37.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then... Why don't you take a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.12,0:33:46.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.63,0:33:51.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you any idea what you\Nput me through, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.63,0:33:54.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I could've drowned, you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.13,0:33:58.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why was there so much water inside the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.64,0:34:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the pressure inside the toilet fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.97,0:34:04.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you never seen that science experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.48,0:34:09.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The one where you place a burning\Ncandle in a bowl filled with water,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.73,0:34:13.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and put a beaker over the candle...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.28,0:34:18.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And when the flame goes out, more and\Nmore water gets sucked into the beaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.32,0:34:19.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The same thing happened here!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.16,0:34:24.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cans burn on the rack inside the airtight toilet,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.29,0:34:29.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the air becomes warmer and expands...\NThe amount of oxygen is reduced,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.33,0:34:31.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and when the flames go out the air\Nbecomes cooler and contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.17,0:34:38.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And to fill that space, the rain water that accumulated is\Nsucked into the toilet through the lower vents. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.72,0:34:40.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that about right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.10,0:34:43.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Science teacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.39,0:34:45.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Masaki Sunami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.27,0:34:54.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First you brought Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} to the\Ntoilet box while walking him to the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.78,0:35:01.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,saying something like "I forgot my keys,\Nso please shelter from the rain inside the toilet."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.24,0:35:06.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Once he was inside, you knocked\Nhim out with a stun gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.50,0:35:11.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and passed a piece of string through his belt,\Nwhich you then tied to the joints of the toilet seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.12,0:35:13.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,preventing Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} from standing up...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.92,0:35:17.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you placed the four cans filled with\Nkerosene on the rack inside the toilet...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.88,0:35:21.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and locked the door using a padlock,\Nputting up the "out of order" sign at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.26,0:35:26.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards you only had to seal\Nthe vents on the back with tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.72,0:35:29.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and close off the drain with a towel,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.39,0:35:32.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the rain water would\Nstart to accumulate, and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.23,0:35:38.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You told Mon'na{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} that he had\Nfallen asleep in the car, an easy lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.03,0:35:41.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and waited for the rain water to gather...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.20,0:35:47.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And after a while, Mon'na{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, who worries easily,\Nwent to go look after Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, all according to plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.12,0:35:50.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, even if she hadn't done\Nso out of her own volition,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.62,0:35:55.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you probably intended go check on him\Nyourself while inviting her along...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.71,0:36:00.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like you had thought, she came back and\Nannounced that Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} wasn't in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:03.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And once everyone started\Nsearching the parking lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.89,0:36:06.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you confirmed that enough\Nrain water had gathered,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.43,0:36:11.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,removed the sign stuck to the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.43,0:36:13.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lit the cans that were placed on the rack,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.85,0:36:16.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and sealed the door with tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.86,0:36:20.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards the rain water\Nwas sucked into the toilet,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.86,0:36:23.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,just like it happened in the experiment,\Ndrowning Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.62,0:36:31.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,While you were going around the bars with Mon'na{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, effectively giving you an alibi,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.91,0:36:36.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then you returned to the parking lot again,\Nremoved the towel from the drain
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.79,0:36:41.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the accumulated water could drain off,\Npeeled off all of the tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.17,0:36:45.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,threw the cans into the bin and cut the string\Nthat had been fastened to Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s belt...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.26,0:36:49.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And in order to hide the fact that\Nthe toilet had been filled with water,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.31,0:36:53.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you placed new toilet paper rolls on the rack,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.94,0:36:59.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,before giving off a scream, as though\Nyou had just discovered the body!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.48,0:37:03.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For this trick to work it is important\Nto find the body as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.86,0:37:08.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the discovery is delayed, the time span\Nfor the estimated time of death widens,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.53,0:37:10.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,nullifying the painstakingly created alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.20,0:37:16.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the murderer must be the person\Nwho discovered the body â€” in other words, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.58,0:37:20.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You are also the only one who could have created\Nthe time for the rain water to accumulate!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.21,0:37:28.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The forensics people are probably retrieving\Nthe tape with your fingerprints right about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.55,0:37:33.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it wasn't in the rubbish bin,\Nyou must have flushed it down the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.31,0:37:36.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And peeling off tape is rather\Ndifficult with gloves on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.94,0:37:38.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that about right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.19,0:37:40.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.86,0:37:42.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.40,0:37:44.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This must be some sort of mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.95,0:37:50.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Sunami has no reason\Nat all to kill Tamba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.49,0:37:51.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.51,0:38:02.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That man let my best friend die without doing anything.\NWhat better motive could there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.71,0:38:07.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-When you say best friend...\NAre you talking about my sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.43,0:38:12.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, your sister, who had\Nplanned to marry that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.39,0:38:18.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But my sister threw herself\Noff a cliff by the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.44,0:38:20.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was even a suicide note...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.73,0:38:23.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She wrote a mail beforehand, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.98,0:38:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saying "The two of us are going away together"...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.32,0:38:31.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That mail wasn't about eloping...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.16,0:38:34.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a double suicide note, saying the two of them\Nwere going away to the next world together!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.62,0:38:41.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, that man suddenly\Nbecame afraid of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.54,0:38:45.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and without trying to help your\Ndrowning sister, he left that cliff...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.13,0:38:47.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.97,0:38:48.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.63,0:38:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When he was drunk that man\Ntold me so without inhibition...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.39,0:38:58.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saying "I'm a hopeless coward" while crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.27,0:39:07.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, even though he's like that...\NMy best friend loved him to death...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.24,0:39:12.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I helped him get there...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.53,0:39:16.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Into the water where she was waiting for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.91,0:40:40.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You went to look for the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.33,0:40:41.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.08,0:40:45.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought you didn't know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.29,0:40:47.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So how did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.50,0:40:51.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it appeared that the\Nkiller was exceptionally strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.88,0:40:55.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I would be able to\Nfeel his killing intent if I saw him...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.93,0:41:03.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if possible you wanted to\Nhave a fight with him, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.19,0:41:07.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, that might have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.19,0:41:09.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He was simply looking for a fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.28,0:41:15.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As I've come to expect of you, Sleeping Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.57,0:41:19.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Solving the case so superbly...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.03,0:41:21.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It was nothing, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.91,0:41:23.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As expected of the true me...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.79,0:41:26.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, but, that experiment...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.25,0:41:30.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That fumbler, he's completely fallen\Nback to his old way of talking...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.42,0:41:35.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well, she took all the good parts though...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.72,0:41:37.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that reminds me, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.18,0:41:40.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge your pants\Nquickly or you'll catch cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.60,0:41:45.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you were just doing your\Ndeductions while sitting in a puddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.02,0:41:51.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's this? I'm soaking wet!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.02,0:41:56.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Uncle, you did say "What does\Nit matter if my pants get wet?"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.36,0:41:58.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I... say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.78,0:42:00.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You did, you did!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.45,0:42:02.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were super cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.66,0:42:04.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Super cool?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.58,0:42:08.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A message... From my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.59,0:42:13.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah, I see... So that's how it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.59,0:42:18.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A PS...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.43,0:42:23.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"PS: Have you already met the wizard?"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.60,0:42:30.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(0,250)}You could say so...
